    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cheap mass-market novels, typically having lurid or sensational subject matter. Originally these such books were issued in shiny yellow paper covers during the Victorian era.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>British English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
